Oluwatosin Omojuyigbe National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, has mourned the death of the Chairman of Globe Motors Limited, Chief Willie Anumudu. Anumudu died on Wednesday. In his condolence message, Tinubu described the late Anumudu as a prominent businessman reputed for his industry and humanitarian activities. “Anumudu was a renowned philanpropist and businessman.  As Chairman of Globe Motors Nigeria Limited, he was reputed for his industry, business expertise and philantropic activities. “He was very close to me. His death is a personal loss. But it is also a distressing loss to the country. Apart from his contributions in the business sector, the country needs people like Anumudu at this critical time when government and private sector players are putting minds and resources together to halt the spread of the coronavirus pandemic and mitigate its effects on our people and economy.” Copyright PUNCH.
